}}

潘洛斯和盧卡斯关于哥德尔不完备定理在人类智能的计算理论方面所具有的含义的观点受到了来自数学家，计算机科学家和哲学家的广泛批评。尽管不同领域的专家会从不同的方面进行批评，<ref>Criticism of the Lucas/Penrose argument that intelligence can not be entirely algorithmic:
* [http://consc.net/mindpapers/6.1b MindPapers: 6.1b. Godelian arguments] {{Wayback|url=http://consc.net/mindpapers/6.1b |date=20110611213335 }}
* [http://users.ox.ac.uk/~jrlucas/Godel/referenc.html References for Criticisms of the Gödelian Argument] {{Wayback|url=http://users.ox.ac.uk/~jrlucas/Godel/referenc.html |date=20200703180031 }}*
* Boolos, George, et al. 1990. ''An Open Peer Commentary on The Emperor's New Mind.'' Behavioral and Brain Sciences 13 (4) 655.
* Davis, Martin 1993. ''How subtle is Gödel's theorem? More on Roger Penrose.'' Behavioral and Brain Sciences, 16, 611-612. Online version at Davis' faculty page at http://cs.nyu.edu/cs/faculty/davism/ {{Wayback|url=http://cs.nyu.edu/cs/faculty/davism/ |date=19981203160909 }}
* Feferman, Solomon 1996. ''[http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.130.7027&rep=rep1&type=pdf Penrose's Gödelian argument] {{Wayback|url=http://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/viewdoc/download?doi=10.1.1.130.7027&rep=rep1&type=pdf |date=20210224121010 }}. PSYCHE 2, 21–32.
* Krajewski, Stanislaw 2007. ''On Gödel's Theorem and Mechanism: Inconsistency or Unsoundness is Unavoidable in any Attempt to 'Out-Gödel' the Mechanist.'' Fundamenta Informaticae 81, 173–181. Reprinted in [http://books.google.com/books?id=0jSS-3Bl06cC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA173#v=onepage&q&f=false Topics in Logic, Philosophy and Foundations of Mathematics and Computer Science:In Recognition of Professor Andrzej Grzegorczyk (2008), p. 173] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=0jSS-3Bl06cC&lpg=PP1&pg=PA173#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20210203044946 }}
* LaForte, Geoffrey, Patrick J. Hayes, and Kenneth M. Ford 1998. ''[http://www.cs.uwf.edu/~glaforte/papers/whyGodel.ps Why Gödel's Theorem Cannot Refute Computationalism] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cs.uwf.edu/~glaforte/papers/whyGodel.ps |date=20060901233518 }}''. Artificial Intelligence, 104:265–286.
* Lewis, David K. 1969. ''[http://www2.units.it/etica/2003_1/7_monographica.doc Lucas against mechanism] {{Wayback|url=http://www2.units.it/etica/2003_1/7_monographica.doc |date=20210225215326 }}''. Philosophy 44 231–233.
* Putnam, Hilary 1995. ''Review of Shadows of the Mind.'' In Bulletin of the American Mathematical Society 32, 370–373（also see Putnam's less technical criticisms in his [http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/04/27/nnp/17540.html New York Times review] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nytimes.com/books/97/04/27/nnp/17540.html |date=20160629121501 }}）
Sources that indicate Penrose's argument is generally rejected:
* Bringsford, S. and Xiao, H. 2000. ''[http://kryten.mm.rpi.edu/refute.Penrose.pdf A Refutation of Penrose's Gödelian Case Against Artificial Intelligence] {{Wayback|url=http://kryten.mm.rpi.edu/refute.Penrose.pdf |date=20210224130103 }}.'' Journal of Experimental and Theoretical Artificial Intelligence 12: 307–329. The authors write that it is "generally agreed" that Penrose "failed to destroy the computational conception of mind."
* In an article at {{cite web |url=http://www.mth.kcl.ac.uk/~llandau/Homepage/Math/Penrose.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2010-10-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010125011300/http://www.mth.kcl.ac.uk/~llandau/Homepage/Math/penrose.html |archivedate=2001-01-25 }} L.J. Landau at the Mathematics Department of King's College London writes that "Penrose's argument, its basis and implications, is rejected by experts in the fields which it touches."
Sources that also note that different sources attack different points of the argument:
* Princeton Philosophy professor John Burgess writes in ''[http://www.princeton.edu/~jburgess/Montreal.doc On the Outside Looking In: A Caution about Conservativeness] {{Wayback|url=http://www.princeton.edu/~jburgess/Montreal.doc |date=20121019093317 }}'' (published in Kurt Gödel: Essays for his Centennial, with the following comments found on [http://books.google.com/books?id=83Attf6BsJ4C&lpg=PP1&pg=PA131#v=onepage&q&f=false pp. 131–132] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=83Attf6BsJ4C&lpg=PP1&pg=PA131#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20210126162259 }}) that "the consensus view of logicians today seems to be that the Lucas–Penrose argument is fallacious, though as I have said elsewhere, there is at least this much to be said for Lucas and Penrose, that logicians are not unanimously agreed as to where precisely the fallacy in their argument lies. There are at least three points at which the argument may be attacked."
* Dershowitz, Nachum 2005. ''[http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/~nachumd/papers/FourSonsOfPenrose.pdf The Four Sons of Penrose] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cs.tau.ac.il/~nachumd/papers/FourSonsOfPenrose.pdf |date=20170809142617 }}'', in ''Proceedings of the Eleventh Conference on Logic Programming for Artificial Intelligence and Reasoning（LPAR; Jamaica）'', G. Sutcliffe and A. Voronkov, eds., Lecture Notes in Computer Science, vol. 3835, Springer-Verlag, Berlin, pp. 125–138.</ref>但上述领域的专家们一致认为潘洛斯/盧卡斯的观点是不成立的。来自[[马文·闵斯基|马文·闵斯基]]（人工智能的主要支持者）的批评尤其激烈：潘洛斯“一章接一章的试图说明人类意识不能基于任何已知的科学原理。”闵斯基的立场与此完全相反——他相信本质上来说人类就是机器：虽然这种机器的功能很复杂，但使用现有的物理学是完全可解释的。闵斯基如此评价潘洛斯：“在科学探索的道路上，仅靠攻击现有的科学知识将无法获取新的原理。但在我看来，这就是潘洛斯的探索手段。”<ref>Marvin Minsky. "Conscious Machines." Machinery of Consciousness, Proceedings, National Research Council of Canada, 75th Anniversary Symposium on Science in Society, June 1991.</ref>

作为对《皇帝新脑》所受到的负面评价的回应，潘洛斯随后出版了《[[意识的阴影|意识的阴影]]》（Shadows of the Mind, 1994）和《[[庞大，渺小，及人类意识|庞大，渺小，及人类意识]]》（The Large, the Small and the Human Mind, 1997）。在这些书中，他还引用了来自麻醉专家[[史都華·哈默洛夫|史都華·哈默洛夫]]的观察。

潘洛斯和史都華·哈默洛夫认为意识是[[微管|微管]]中量子引力效应的结果。该过程被他们称为 [[Orch-OR|Orch-OR]]（orchestrated objective reduction，暂译：谐客观化归）。此后，在《[[物理评论E|物理评论E]]》上，[[马克斯·泰格马克|马克斯·泰格马克]]发文指出，微管中神经元激发和兴奋的时间尺度以最少 10,000,000,000 倍的因子慢于[[量子退相干|量子退相干]]时间。<ref>Tegmark, Max. 2000. "The importance of quantum decoherence in brain processes". Physical Review E. vol 61. pp. 4194–4206.</ref>马克斯·泰格马克的论文受到了广泛接受，有文章如此总结：“没有卷入这场争斗的物理学家们——比如 IBM 的 Jone A. Smolin——认为文中的计算解决了长久以来的怀疑。‘我们拥有的并不是一颗接近绝对零值的大脑。从合理性上来讲人类大脑不可能以量子方式进化’”。<ref name="Tetlow 2007 166">{{cite book | url=http://books.google.com/?id=3mPI9rUuhJ8C&printsec=frontcover&dq=Penrose+%22thought+process%22&q=Penrose%20 | last=Tetlow | first=Philip | title=The Web's Awake: An Introduction to the Field of Web Science and the Concept of Web Life|publisher=John Wiley & Sons | location=Hoboken, NJ | year=2007 | isbn=978-0-470-13794-9 | page=166}}</ref>马克斯·泰格马克的论文被潘洛斯-哈默洛夫的批评者们广泛引用。

物理学家 Scott Hagan、Jack Tuszynski 和史都華·哈默洛夫也在《物理评论E》上发文回应马克斯·泰格马克，<ref name="Hagan2002">{{cite journal | doi=10.1103/PhysRevE.65.061901 | author=Hagan, S., Hameroff, S., and Tuszyński, J. | title=Quantum Computation in Brain Microtubules? Decoherence and Biological Feasibility | journal=Physical Review E | volume=65 | pages=061901 | arxiv=quant-ph/0005025 | year=2002| bibcode = 2002PhRvE..65f1901H }}</ref>声称马克斯·泰格马克检验的并不是 Orch-OR 模型，而是他自己构造的模型：马克斯·泰格马克的计算中涉及的量子叠加态（the superpositions of quanta）以 24 纳米分隔，而非 Orch-OR 所要求的小的多的分隔。按照 Orch-OR 规定的量子叠加态进行运算之后，史都華·哈默洛夫的团队宣布新的量子退相干所需的时间尺度要比马克斯·泰格马克的结果大 7 个级数。但这个结果依然比所需的时间少了 25 毫秒——如果想要使量子过程如同 Orch-OR 所描述的那样，能够和 40 赫兹的伽玛同步产生关联的话。为了弥补这一环节，史都華·哈默洛夫等人做了一系列假设和提议。首先他们假设微管内部可以在[[液态|液态]]和[[凝胶态|凝胶态]]之间互相转换。在凝胶状态下，他们进一步假设水的电偶极子会沿着微管外围的微管蛋白同向排列。史都華·哈默洛夫认为这种有序排列的水将会屏蔽微管蛋白中任何量子退相干过程。每个微管蛋白还会从微管中延伸出一条带负电荷的“尾巴”，从而可以吸引带正电荷的离子。这可以进一步屏蔽量子退相干的过程。除此之外，还有推测认为微管可在生物能的驱使下进入相干态。

[[File:Penrose_in_University_of_Santiago_de_Compostela_to_picked_up_the_Fonseca_prize.jpg|thumb]]接受 Fonseca 奖]]

最终，有建议认为微管的构造或许适用于[[量子纠错|量子纠错]]（quantum error correction），一种可将量子相干性和环境交互能力结合起来的手段。在最近的十年里，一些同情潘洛斯的研究者提出了若干适用于微管量子过程的替代方案。这些方案认为微管蛋白的“尾巴”可以和微管相关的蛋白质（motor proteins和presynaptic scaffold proteins）发生作用。这些提议的优势在于可在马克斯·泰格马克的量子退相干时间尺度内发生。

史都華·哈默洛夫在 Google Tech 关于量子生物学的系列讲座中给出了该领域近期研究的总结，结果再次招致对 Orch-OR 模型的批评。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LXFFbxoHp3s |title=存档副本 |access-date=2012-07-07 |archive-date=2020-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201228051352/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LXFFbxoHp3s |dead-url=no }}</ref>除此之外，潘洛斯和史都華·哈默洛夫在一篇发表于 2011 年的论文中，参考之前所受到的批评，给出了 Orch-OR 理论的修改模型；该论文还探讨了意识在宇宙中占有的地位。<ref name="Hameroff-Penrose 2011">{{cite web | url=http://www.quantumconsciousness.org/Cosmology160.html | title=存档副本 | accessdate=2012-08-13 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616045402/http://www.quantumconsciousness.org/Cosmology160.html | archivedate=2012-06-16 }}</ref>

尽管作为潘洛斯观点的支持者，但根据闵斯基和科学专栏作家[[查爾斯·塞費|查爾斯·塞費]]（Charles Seife）的评价，Phillip Tetlow 依然认为潘洛斯关于人类意识过程的看法在科学界属于“少数派观点”。Seife 把潘洛斯描述成“一小撮相信意识的本质是量子过程的科学家”之一。

2014 年 1 月，史都華·哈默洛夫和潘洛斯主張，日本物質材料研究中心的博士 Anirban Bandyopadhyay 所发现的微管中的量子振荡证实了 Orch-OR 假说。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Anirban_Bandyopadhyay | title=Anirban Bandyopadhyay | publisher=[[ResearchGate|ResearchGate]] | accessdate=2014-02-22 | archive-date=2015-02-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150220224402/http://www.researchgate.net/profile/Anirban_Bandyopadhyay | dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2014/01/140116085105.htm | title=Discovery of quantum vibrations in 'microtubules' inside brain neurons supports controversial theory of consciousness | publisher=''ScienceDaily'' | accessdate=2014-02-22 | archive-date=2015-12-17 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151217233934/http://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2014/01/140116085105.htm | dead-url=no }}</ref>这个理论的修订更正版伴随著批评和辩论发表在《''Physics of Life Reviews''》。<ref name=Hameroff2014>{{cite journal | author1=S. Hameroff | author2=R. Penrose | title=Consciousness in the universe: A review of the 'Orch OR' theory | journal=Physics of Life Reviews | date=2014 | volume=11 | issue=1 | pages=39–78 | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1571064513001188 | accessdate=2014-03-29 | pmid=24070914 | doi=10.1016/j.plrev.2013.08.002 | bibcode=2014PhLRv..11...39H | archive-date=2014-07-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140729220020/http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1571064513001188 | dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 宗教信仰 ==

潘洛斯是一个[[无神论者|无神论者]]。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.samharris.org/site/book_letter_to_christian_nation/ | last=Harris | first=Sam | authorlink=Sam Harris (author) | title=Letter to A Christian Nation | work=SamHarrisOrg | accessdate=2020-06-05 | archive-date=2010-12-29 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229071338/http://www.samharris.org/site/book_letter_to_christian_nation/ | dead-url=no}} Quoting Penrose's blurb for Harris's book ''Letter to a Christian Nation''.</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_9032000/9032626.stm | title=Big Bang follows Big Bang follows Big Bang | accessdate=2010-12-01 | work=BBC News | date=2010-09-25 | archive-date=2010-11-30 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101130152519/http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_9032000/9032626.stm | dead-url=no }}.</ref>在纪录片{{tsl|en|A Brief History of Time (film)|时间简史}}（''A Brief History of Time''）中，潘洛斯说道：{{Quote|“我认为宇宙是有目的的，它的出现不可能是机缘巧合……有些人认为宇宙''就是会''存在，而且''就是会''运转——有点类似某种计算过程，然后我们不知道怎么的，就意外出现在宇宙中。但是我认为在看待宇宙的问题上，这些看法并不具有建设意义，我认为关于宇宙一定有什么更深刻的东西。”<ref>See [http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=-5382609196671955257# A Brief History of Time] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120225152533/http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=-5382609196671955257 |date=2012-02-25 }}, quote starts at about 1:12:43 in the video.</ref>}}

潘洛斯还是[[British_Humanist_Association|英国人道协会]]的杰出支持者。

== 獲獎 ==
[[File:RogerPenrose_CapturingInfinity_cropped.jpg|thumb]]
羅傑·潘洛斯因對科學的貢獻獲頒多個獎項。
* 1971年，[[丹尼·海涅曼数学物理奖|丹尼·海涅曼数学物理奖]]
* 1972年，[[皇家學會|皇家學會]]會員；
* 1975年，[[愛丁頓獎章|愛丁頓獎章]](他与[[史蒂芬·霍金|史蒂芬·霍金]]共同獲獎)
* 1985年，[[皇家獎章|皇家獎章]]
* 1988年，[[沃爾夫物理學獎|沃爾夫物理學獎]](他与[[史蒂芬·霍金|史蒂芬·霍金]]共同獲獎)
* 1988年，[[狄拉克奖|狄拉克奖]]
* 2000年，[[功績勳章_(英國)|功績勳章 (英國)]]
* 2004年，[[德摩根奖章|德摩根奖章]]
* 2005年，[[波蘭|波蘭]][[華沙大學|華沙大學]]與[[比利時|比利時]][[荷語天主教魯汶大學|荷語天主教魯汶大學]]兩所大學的[[榮譽博士|榮譽博士]]學位（Honoris Causa）。
* 2006年，[[狄拉克奖|狄拉克奖]]（來自[[新南威爾士大學|新南威爾士大學]]）
* 2008年，[[科普利獎章|科普利獎章]], 和[[科睿唯安引文桂冠獎|科睿唯安引文桂冠獎]]
* 2020年，獲得[[诺贝尔物理学奖|诺贝尔物理学奖]]並得到一半的獎金，授與原因為他發現黑洞的形成是广义相对论的有力預測。<ref name=nobel2020/>

